cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about training a Deep Convolutional Neural Network (DCNN) for biomedical semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses different normalization methods for training the DCNN, which is related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional kernels, which is related to neural networks, hence cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses three datasets for validation, which is related to multimedia, hence cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
